'''Kamaruzaman Mohamad''' (1961 â€” April 28, 2014) was a Malaysian journalist and editor for [[Utusan Malaysia]].

In 2000, Mohamad won the ''Kajai Award'' for being the first Malaysian journalist to penetrate the Militant Islamist separatist group [[Abu Sayyaf]].

Mohamad died on April 28, 2014 at [[Subang Jaya]] Medical Centre from a kidney ailment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bernama.com/bernama/v7/ge/newsgeneral.php?id=1034103|title=Former Processing Editor Of Utusan Malaysia, Kamaruzaman Mohamad Dies|publisher=Bernama.com|accessdate=2014-04-28}}</ref>  He was 53.

